Common Beginner Mistakes
❌ Forgetting to return JSX
missing return.
function App() {
    return <h1>Hello</h1>;
}
❌ Returning multiple elements without a parent
without div
❌ Using class instead of className

Key Points
React applications are built using components.
A component returns JSX.
JSX describes what should appear on the screen.
main.jsx renders the root component (App).
JavaScript expressions are written inside {}.
Multiple JSX elements must be wrapped in a single parent element or a React Fragment.


Interview Answer
A React application starts with the App component, which returns JSX describing the UI. 
The main.jsx file renders this component into the root element in index.html.
React then converts the JSX into browser-renderable elements and displays the user interface.
